365→<section class="section reveal" id="problem">
366→  <div class="tag">The problem</div>
367→  <h2>You are the integration layer<br>between your AI agents</h2>
368→  <p style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">You already use AI agents. Your coding agent writes your code. Your chat assistant helps you think through architecture. Your editor agent autocompletes. But none of them share context.</p>
369→  <ul class="problem-list">
370→    <li><span class="arrow">→</span> Copy error logs from CI into your coding agent</li>
371→    <li><span class="arrow">→</span> Relay architecture decisions from a chat into your codebase</li>
372→    <li><span class="arrow">→</span> Manually track what was decided, what's blocked, what changed</li>
373→    <li><span class="arrow">→</span> Re-explain project state every time you start a new session</li>
374→    <li><span class="arrow">→</span> Context-switch between tools, losing continuity at every step</li>
375→  </ul>
376→  <p style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:1rem;">Every agent you add makes it worse. Brain fixes this — not by replacing your agents, but by giving them shared memory.</p>
377→</section>
