381→<!-- AGENTS -->
382→<section class="section-wide reveal" id="agents">
383→  <div class="tag tag-center">Specialized agents</div>
384→  <h2 class="center">A coordinated workforce, not a chatbot</h2>
385→  <p class="subtitle">Each agent has a role, a domain, and authority scopes. They coordinate through the knowledge graph — not through you.</p>
386→  <div class="agent-grid">
387→    <div class="agent-card">
388→      <h3>Architect</h3>
389→      <div class="agent-role">CTO / CPO</div>
390→      <p>Technical decisions, system design, architecture constraints. Checks implementations against what was decided. Resolves conflicts between competing approaches.</p>
391→    </div>
392→    <div class="agent-card">
393→      <h3>Strategist</h3>
394→      <div class="agent-role">CEO / CSO</div>
395→      <p>Market positioning, pricing, GTM, competitive response. Challenges product decisions against business viability. Catches positioning drift before it compounds.</p>
396→    </div>
397→    <div class="agent-card">
398→      <h3>Management</h3>
399→      <div class="agent-role">COO</div>
400→      <p>Task tracking, priority management, execution velocity. Flags blocked work, stale decisions, and resource conflicts. Keeps the machine running.</p>
401→    </div>
402→    <div class="agent-card">
403→      <h3>Coding Agents</h3>
404→      <div class="agent-role">Via MCP · Cursor, Aider, Codex, and others</div>
405→      <p>Your existing tools connected to the graph. Context injected on session start. Decisions, observations, and questions flow back automatically.</p>
406→    </div>
407→    <div class="agent-card">
408→      <h3>Design Partner</h3>
409→      <div class="agent-role">Early-stage co-designer</div>
410→      <p>Brainstorms product ideas, asks probing questions, identifies gaps. Shapes vague ideas into structured projects, features, and decisions in the graph.</p>
411→    </div>
412→    <div class="agent-card">
413→      <h3>Observer</h3>
414→      <div class="agent-role">Background intelligence</div>
415→      <p>Scans the graph for patterns nobody asked about. Stale decisions, cross-project conflicts, missing coverage, priority drift. Surfaces observations that compound into suggestions.</p>
416→    </div>
417→  </div>
418→</section>
