491→<!-- CONCEPTS -->
492→<section class="section-wide reveal">
493→  <div class="tag tag-center">Key concepts</div>
494→  <h2 class="center">Built different</h2>
495→  <p class="subtitle">The primitives that make coordination possible.</p>
496→  <div class="concept-grid">
497→    <div class="concept">
498→      <h3>⬡ Decisions</h3>
499→      <p>Every decision is tracked — who made it, why, and what alternatives were considered. Agents propose. Humans confirm. Nothing falls through the cracks.</p>
500→    </div>
501→    <div class="concept">
502→      <h3>◉ Observations</h3>
503→      <p>"I noticed X." Agents surface contradictions, gaps, patterns, and risks as they work. Observations accumulate and compound into actionable suggestions.</p>
504→    </div>
505→    <div class="concept">
506→      <h3>⊞ Projects, Features &amp; Tasks</h3>
507→      <p>Work breaks down hierarchically. Agents decompose tasks at runtime. Status rolls up automatically. You see progress without tracking it.</p>
508→    </div>
509→    <div class="concept">
510→      <h3>✦ Suggestions</h3>
511→      <p>Agents tell you what you should be thinking about. Accept a suggestion and it becomes a task, decision, or feature — with full trace back to the evidence.</p>
512→    </div>
513→    <div class="concept">
514→      <h3>? Questions</h3>
515→      <p>When an agent doesn't know, it asks instead of guessing. You answer. The answer becomes a decision in the graph. No stalling, no silent assumptions.</p>
516→    </div>
517→    <div class="concept">
518→      <h3>💬 Conversations</h3>
519→      <p>Every chat produces structured knowledge. Conversations group by project automatically. Branch when topics diverge. Find anything by following the graph, not scrolling history.</p>
520→    </div>
521→    <div class="concept">
522→      <h3>⟠ Commits</h3>
523→      <p>Code is linked to the decisions and tasks it implements. Contradictions are caught before they land. Every change has a trail back to the intent behind it.</p>
524→    </div>
525→    <div class="concept">
526→      <h3>△ Authority Scopes</h3>
527→      <p>Control what each agent can do without asking. Start restrictive. Expand trust over time. You set the boundary — agents stay within it.</p>
528→    </div>
529→    <div class="concept">
530→      <h3>◇ Living Descriptions</h3>
531→      <p>Descriptions update themselves. Ship a feature — the project summary reflects it. Confirm a decision — related entities incorporate it. No one writes status updates.</p>
532→    </div>
533→    <div class="concept">
534→      <h3>⟡ Cross-Project Intelligence</h3>
535→      <p>Conflicts between projects surface automatically. Duplicate work gets flagged. A decision in one project that breaks another is caught before anyone notices manually.</p>
536→    </div>
537→    <div class="concept">
538→      <h3>⊕ Agent Sessions</h3>
539→      <p>Every session is remembered. The next agent knows what the last one did — what was decided, what questions came up, what got built. Context carries forward.</p>
540→    </div>
541→    <div class="concept">
542→      <h3>⟐ Identity</h3>
543→      <p>One person across all tools. Your Slack, GitHub, and terminal sessions all resolve to the same identity. Agents act on your behalf with scoped permissions.</p>
544→    </div>
545→  </div>
546→</section>
